# Files `wt step copy-ignored` copies into a new worktree (run by the pre-start
# hook in .config/wt.toml). A file is copied only if it is BOTH gitignored AND
# matched here — the allow-list of setup artifacts a fresh `git worktree` lacks.
# NOTE: .work/ is deliberately absent — it's symlinked to the main checkout by
# the pre-start hook, never copied.
#
# Patterns are gitignore-style — NO inline comments (a trailing `# …` becomes
# part of the pattern). Keep comments on their own line.

# installed deps (copy beats a cold `npm install`)
node_modules/
# local-only agent settings (per-machine permission grants)
.claude/settings.local.json
# editor settings
.vscode/
